            "abstract": [
                {
                    "value": "Lini M. De Vries (1905-1982) was a nurse, public health administrator, author and educator who served as a nurse with the Medical Bureau to Aid Spanish Democracy (AMB) during the Spanish Civil War.  The collection contains correspondence, clippings, a literary draft, and Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) files obtained through the Freedom of Information Act (FOIA).",
